# Movepress CLI smoke tests

```console
$ movepress --help
Synchronize WordPress environments with a modern Wordmove-inspired CLI.

Usage: movepress [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  push  Push changes from the source environment into the destination
  pull  Pull changes from the source environment into the destination
  help  Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --config <PATH>  Path to Movefile.toml configuration [default: Movefile.toml]
  -v, --verbose        Enable verbose logging
      --dry-run        Preview the operation without applying changes
  -y, --yes            Automatically confirm destructive operations for non-production targets
  -h, --help           Print help
  -V, --version        Print version

$ movepress push db local production --dry-run
Dry Run Summary
===============
Config   : Movefile.toml
Operation: push database from 'local' to 'production'
Scope    : database
Source   : local
Target   : production

File Sync Plan
--------------
- Not included for the selected scope.

Database Plan
-------------
- Would dump the source database from 'local'.
- Would import into 'production' after applying required confirmations.
- Would optionally run WP-CLI search-replace if configured.

Database Sync Preview
=====================
Mode       : dry-run
Source     : local (127.0.0.1:3306 / movepress_local)
Target     : production (localhost:3306 / movepress_production)
Transport  : local → remote (ssh)
Compression: enabled (gzip)
Pipeline
--------
Dump   : [local] MYSQL_PWD=**** "mysqldump" "--host=127.0.0.1" "--port=3306" "--user=root" "--single-transaction" "--quick" "--skip-lock-tables" "--default-character-set=utf8mb4" "movepress_local"
Filter  1: [local] "gzip" "-c"
Import : [ssh deploy@production.example.com:22] MYSQL_PWD=**** "bash" "-lc" "set -o pipefail; gzip -cd | "mysql" "--host=localhost" "--port=3306" "--user=movepress" "--default-character-set=utf8mb4" "movepress_production"
Staging
-------
- Streaming pipeline between source and destination; no temp files created.
WP-CLI
------
- Target environment 'production' does not define wp_cli; skipping WP-CLI stage.

$ movepress push uploads local staging --dry-run --verbose
Dry Run Summary
===============
Config   : Movefile.toml
Operation: push uploads from 'local' to 'staging'
Scope    : uploads
Source   : local
Target   : staging
Verbose  : enabled

File Sync Plan
--------------
- Would build local and remote manifests for 'uploads'.
- Would compute file deltas to transfer efficiently.
- Would honor excludes from Movefile.toml.

Database Plan
-------------
- Not included for the selected scope.

File Sync Preview
=================
Scope  : uploads
Mode   : dry-run
- Preview skipped executing rsync to avoid contacting remote hosts.
Source : local ([CWD]/tests/fixtures/local/wp-content/uploads)
Target : staging (deploy@staging.example.com:/var/www/movepress/wp-content/uploads)
Command: 'rsync' '-a' '--stats' '--dry-run' '-v' '-z' '--exclude-from' '[excludes-file]' '[CWD]/tests/fixtures/local/wp-content/uploads/' 'deploy@staging.example.com:/var/www/movepress/wp-content/uploads/'
Excludes: **/*.log, **/.DS_Store, wp-content/uploads/cache/**

$ movepress pull content staging local --dry-run
Dry Run Summary
===============
Config   : Movefile.toml
Operation: pull wp-content from 'staging' to 'local'
Scope    : wp-content
Source   : staging
Target   : local

File Sync Plan
--------------
- Would build local and remote manifests for 'wp-content'.
- Would compute file deltas to transfer efficiently.
- Would honor excludes from Movefile.toml.

Database Plan
-------------
- Not included for the selected scope.

File Sync Preview
=================
Scope  : wp-content
Mode   : dry-run
- Preview skipped executing rsync to avoid contacting remote hosts.
Source : staging (deploy@staging.example.com:/var/www/movepress/wp-content)
Target : local ([CWD]/tests/fixtures/local/wp-content)
Command: 'rsync' '-a' '--stats' '--dry-run' '-z' '--exclude-from' '[excludes-file]' 'deploy@staging.example.com:/var/www/movepress/wp-content/' '[CWD]/tests/fixtures/local/wp-content/'
Excludes: **/*.log, **/.DS_Store, wp-content/uploads/cache/**

$ env PATH="$PWD/tests/fixtures/bin:$PATH" movepress push db local staging --yes --config tests/cmd/fixtures/local-db.toml
Auto-confirmed database operation for non-production target 'staging'.

WP-CLI stub: search-replace https://local.test https://staging.test --skip-columns=guid
Database Sync Result
====================
Mode       : active
Source     : local (127.0.0.1:3306 / local_db)
Target     : staging (127.0.0.1:3306 / staging_db)
Transport  : local → local
Compression: disabled
Pipeline
--------
Dump   : [local] MYSQL_PWD=**** "mysqldump" "--host=127.0.0.1" "--port=3306" "--user=root" "--single-transaction" "--quick" "--skip-lock-tables" "--default-character-set=utf8mb4" "local_db"
Import : [local] MYSQL_PWD=**** "mysql" "--host=127.0.0.1" "--port=3306" "--user=root" "--default-character-set=utf8mb4" "staging_db"
Staging
-------
- Streaming pipeline between source and destination; no temp files created.
WP-CLI
------
search-replace https://local.test -> https://staging.test
Command   : [local] (cd tests/fixtures/staging) "wp" "search-replace" "https://local.test" "https://staging.test" "--skip-columns=guid"
- WP-CLI search-replace executed successfully.

$ movepress push db local production --yes
? failed
Error: Destination 'production' is marked as production. Interactive confirmation is required.

$ movepress push db local production
? failed
Error: Refusing to run push database from 'local' to 'production' without confirmation. Re-run interactively or pass --yes for non-production targets.

$ movepress push db local staging --config tests/cmd/fixtures/missing.toml --dry-run
? failed
Error: Movefile not found at 'tests/cmd/fixtures/missing.toml'. Provide a valid path with --config.

```
